700785f-a.title: Bronx: College Avenue - 145th Street (East)
700785f-a.text:
College Avenue, west side, from East 146th(right) to East 145th
Str ets, looking south and showing Public SChool Noll. The
school occupies a triangular plot bounded by the three above
mentioned thoroughfares.
(2)shows the school as seen from the intersection of 146th and
145th Streets, the former being on the left and the later on
the right.
P. L. Sperr  April 29, 1941
No Reproduct ions  Views 1,2

700784f-b.title: Bronx: College Avenue - 145th Street (East)
700784f-b.text:
College Avenue, east side, north from E. 145th to E.146th Streets,
showing consecutively, St. Ritas Roman Cathalic Church, the
rectory, and St. Ritas School. View 2 shows the church alone
and views 3 and 4 the parochial school, view 4 being from
E. 146th Street.
P. L. Sperr  April 28, 1941
NO REPROODUCTICNS  Views 1-4
